Feature: Repello Muggletum (Muggle-Repelling Charm)

    Keeps Muggles away from wizarding places by causing them to remember
    important meetings they missed and to cause the Muggles in question to
    forget what they were doing in the first place.

    Pronunciation:
        /rɛˈpɛloʊ ˈmʊɡlətəm/ re-PEL-oh MUG-lə-təm
    Seen/mentioned:
        Mentioned in Quidditch Through the Ages as being used to keep Muggles
        away from the Quidditch World Cup. Hogwarts was also said to be guarded
        by the Muggle-Repelling Charm. Harry and Hermione also use it on
        numerous occasions, among many other spells, to protect and hide their
        campsite in Deathly Hallows.
